Text:
@walowalo94 Hari dalam Hijri start maghrib sebab ia guna Lunar Calendar.

Bulan baharu dikira pada bulan mula-mula kelihatan iaitu biasanya waktu sunset.

Masihi guna matahari masa tamadun mesir dulu. Matahari tertinggi 12pm. Jadi 12am adalah bertentangan dan dikira permulaan hari.

Translated Text:
@walowalo94 Hijri days start at maghrib because it uses the Lunar Calendar.

The new moon is counted when the moon first appears, which is usually at sunset.

Still using the sun during the ancient Egyptian civilization. Highest sun 12pm. So 12am is the opposite and counts as the start of the day.

